                  </hi>. I am horse-keeper at the Hats public-house, at Eal<lb></lb>ing. On the 23rd of January I placed my hat and handkerchief on the corn-bin in the passage—there was a fight between some labourers about half-past eleven o'clock at night—the prisoner was there—I missed my hat and handkerchief—I found my hat next morning.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> When you got your hat was it not torn? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, all to pieces—I saw the handkerchief at the station, and it is mine.</p>
